<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-10-18T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-10-18T10:00:00-05:00" n="449" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d449">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">832.00 Revolutions/96: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de
                                        Janeiro</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-10-18T12:00:00-03:00">October 18,
                                1930—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received October
                            18—noon.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>107. Department’s telegram No. 65 [<hi rend="italic">67</hi>], October
                            17, 3 p.m. Am I instructed to inform the Brazilian Government according,
                            to custom that the U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Pensacola</hi> will call
                            at Pará, Pernambuco, and Bahia?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>